# What are the rules of studying?

* Use recall.
* Test yourself (flash cards all the time).
* Use spaced repitition.
* Vary the study material often.
* Try and explain the material in simplistic terms, as if to a child or layperson.
* Eat your frogs first.
* Put your progress in context when motivation lacks.
* Focus hard, and take regular breaks (pomodoro)
* Don't allow *any* distractions.
* Don't re-read passively.
* Don't assume you know something when you're looking at the answer already.
* Don't cram.
* Don't stick to things you already know.

